# Example crontab wiring the boot-autostart pattern together.
# Install with:  crontab crontab.example   (or `crontab -e` and paste).
# Adjust the ~/myproject paths to your real project location.

# --- Boot: start everything once when the machine comes up --------------------
# Model / API servers (health-waited launcher).
@reboot ~/myproject/start_servers.sh >> ~/myproject/logs/boot.log 2>&1
# Bot gateway (flock single-instance; foreground process holds the lock).
@reboot ~/myproject/start_gateway.sh
# Persistent-connection worker (flock single-instance).
@reboot ~/myproject/start_watcher.sh

# --- Watchdogs: keep them up if they die or wedge -----------------------------
# Gateway watchdog: re-run the launcher every 5 min. flock makes it a no-op if up.
*/5 * * * * ~/myproject/start_gateway.sh # gateway watchdog

# Worker watchdog: socket-aware, every 1 min. Restarts on a dead process OR a
# wedged (socket-less) connection. See src/watchdog.sh.
*/1 * * * * ~/myproject/watchdog.sh # worker watchdog (socket-aware)

# Silence cron's default mail; the scripts log to their own files instead.
MAILTO=""
